Mick Philpott, 55, shook his head from
side to side when the charges were read. He leaned forward to blow a 
kiss to one of his relatives and mouthed an obscenity at detectives 
before leaving the court.

Three weeks ago he had been hailed as a
hero credited with ‘valiant’ attempts to save the children as fire 
swept through the three-bedroom council house.

Back in May 2003, when the couple 
married in a church near Derby, with four-year-old Duwayne as a pageboy 
and baby Jade as a bridesmaid, family and friends gathered to join the 
celebration.

Yesterday some of those same people 
were among 21 who filed solemnly into Court One at Southern Derbyshire 
magistrates court to see the pair face accusations of murder.

