Yesterday the hearing – the first time the 
couple have been brought to court since being charged – began with the 
sound of footsteps and the rattle of chains as a door swung open into 
the dock. Mick Philpott walked in first. He wore tracksuit trousers and a
sleeveless grey vest that showed off the tattoos on otherwise bare 
arms. A small, slight, man, he was dwarfed by the security guard to whom
he was handcuffed.

It took just a few paces to get from 
one end of the dock to the other but he covered the distance with a 
slight swagger, like an amateur fighter entering the ring.

Mairead was led in behind him. Even away from the female guards who flanked her, she looked tiny.

